    "body": "You're misunderstanding the nuances of the English language, I guess. Fair use was pretty much written for uses like ours. Please read Section 4, I think it will interest you.\n\nOn 2015-08-26, at 1:37 AM, Matthias Mailänder notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> http://redalert1.com/ has something like that in the footer in some kind of disclaimer style. However I doubt the \"fair use\" term from US jurisdiction applies. If you read the legal text:\n> \n> for purposes such as criticism, comment, news reporting, teaching (including multiple copies for classroom use), scholarship, or research, is not an infringement of copyright\n> \n> That doesn't really fit here.\n> \n> —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub.\n"
