    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It does hurt potential sales. Although this might sound stupid - I'm kinda affected by East-European mentality here, which does not believe in Digital Piracy Is Evil and also personally had some really sad examples of No Export For You to always have a second thought about DPIE - our D2k looks pretty D2k for the casual play-for-fun people who thereby no longer would buy the real thing. That sounds pretty solid as a reason on a court to me.\n\nOn the other hand, if there would be a simple way to know that it's out of print, and only 2nd-hand sources are available, then I guess fair use can be applied - the IP owners can't get further profit since they got all the money they could gather from the actual games already.\n"
